                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Moving Jonas's entrance ~150 words earlier would tighten the opening without losing Maren's interiority. Right now the reader spends 500 words alone with her before any external tension arrives. Consider having him appear while she's still at the window — interrupting her contemplation creates a stronger contrast.",
