                          "content": "The pacing itself is fine — the problem is sensory narrowness. The first 400 words rely almost entirely on sight (glazed streets, clouds, watching). Adding a sound or tactile detail every 2-3 sentences would create rhythm without speeding up the scene. The stillness you're building is effective, but it needs texture to feel inhabited rather than described.",
